The paper deals with the design of a new framework for Device-to-Device (D2D) coded caching networks, which involves optimization of rate and reduction of subpacketizations. This topic is closely related to information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the partitioning of D2D users into multiple groups, which can be seen as a clustering problem (cs.SI). The proposed framework involves careful selection of transmitters within each multicasting group, which can be viewed as an optimization problem (cs.DC). Finally, the paper presents a new design framework for D2D caching schemes, which can be seen as a contribution to machine learning (cs.LG).
